{
  "texts": [
    "Sputum smear microscopy imagesA viscous fluid called sputum is produced in the lungs and air passages, which is a crucial factor in the progression of certain lung disorders.",
    "Sputum smear microscopy has generally been considered the most effective approach for diagnosing lung diseases like TB.",
    "Specimens of sputum expectorated by patients with symptoms are placed chemically onto plain glass microscope slides [8].",
    "Then, they are analyzed by laboratory procedures that identify acid-fast bacteria (AFB), like Mycobacterium TB cells [86].",
    "The images obtained from a sputum smear test are often obtained via fluorescence microscopy or conventional microscopy."
  ]
}